HEADWORD: Ginglymodi
<hw>Gin`gly*mo"di</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.; cf.
Gr. <?/ ginglymoid. See <er>Ginglymoid</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An order of ganoid fishes, including the modern gar pikes and many
allied fossil forms. They have rhombic, ganoid scales, a heterocercal
tail, paired fins without an axis, fulcra on the fins, and a bony
skeleton, with the vertebr⟦ae⟧ convex in front and concave behind,
forming a ball and socket joint. See <er>Ganoidel</er>.</def></p>

<p><ent>Ginglymoidal</ent>⟦br⟧
